Subject: [PATCH] Fix singular matrix crash: adaptive regularization for
 covariance inversion
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Replace all bare `sigma + eps*I → linalg.inv()` patterns with `_safe_spd_inv()`
which uses adaptive regularization: max(eps, eps * ||diag(Σ)||_∞).

Root cause: with GL(K) transport operators, Ω·Σ·Ωᵀ can produce covariance
matrices where eps=1e-6 on the diagonal is negligible compared to the matrix
scale, leaving the regularized matrix effectively singular.

The new `_safe_spd_inv()` function:
- Scales regularization proportional to the matrix diagonal magnitude
- Falls back to pseudoinverse if inv() still fails
- Replaces 6 fragile inv() call sites in variational_ffn.py

https://claude.ai/code/session_011wk1LywVCwdT2hGGHoQYPp
